<title>SOUTH AFRICA: S.African car workers agree wages deal.</title>
<headline>S.African car workers agree wages deal.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-07-03</dateline>
<text>
<p>South Africa's Automobile Manufacturers Employers Association said on Thursday it had struck a wages deal with two unions effective from July 1.</p>
<p>The deal, with the National Union of Metal Workers of South Afra and the South African Workers Union, covers 25,000 hourly paid workers at South Africa's seven motor manufacturing plants.</p>
<p>The across-the-board wage increase gives employees in skill levels 1-4 a 9.5 percent rise and those in levels 5-7 an 8.5 percent hike.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482 1003</p>
